      • provideFor

        public java.util.Set<Arbitrary<?>> provideFor(TypeUsage targetType,
                                              ArbitraryProvider.SubtypeProvider subtypeProvider)
        Description copied from interface: ArbitraryProvider
        This is the method you must override in your own implementations of ArbitraryProvider. It should return a set of arbitrary instances for a given targetType. Only targetTypes that have been allowed by ArbitraryProvider.canProvideFor(TypeUsage) will be given to this method. subtypeProvider can be used to get the arbitraries for any type argument of targetType.
